name: Añejo Tequila
description:
A golden full-bodied with silver reflections. 

Clearly defined by the aroma of slow cooked agave and a delicate oak barrel endnote. 
In the mouth, all its aromatic fullness unwinds. All this is the result of the great care that our tequila is subjected during its 24 months of aging.

name: Blanco Tequila
description: Intensely brilliant and luminous, with silvery hues and strong body, allows enjoying its excellent distillation, leaving a trail of scents with a subtle endnote of cooked agave. Either straight or mixed, the nature of agave stands at all times.

name: Rioja Crianza
description:
Visual : Intense red colour with tawny hues.

Nose : Intense, elegant with ripe fruit and undergrowth scents. You can
find aromas of spices, butter and vanilla from the oak barrel ageing.

Taste : Elegant, mellow, fresh, ripe, with velvety tannins.

name: Rioja Reserva
description:
Appearence : Tawny Color With A Medium Robe Ruby Trims, Clean And Bright.

Aroma : Medium Intensity With Aromas Of Licorice, Fruit Passes, Roasted Coffee And Cocoa.

Taste : Good Structure, Balanced Acidity, Soft And Round Tannins With A Long And Complex Aftertaste.

name: Rioja Tempranillo
description:
Appearance:  Intense cherry red color with high robe and garnet rim.

Aroma :  Medium-high intensity and stands out for its red fruit and floral notes in perfect harmony with the elegant toastes and vainilla notes from its time in oak barriques.

Taste : Fresh, round, elegant with very ripe tannins and long aftertaste.

name: Cellar Selection Pinot Noir Hawke's Bay
description: Varietal berry and ripe cherry aromas, with vibrant flavors of red berries and spice. A fresh and lively palate, with silky tannins and a lingering finish.

name: Cellars Selection Sauvignon Blanc
description: Aromas and flavors of ripe passionfruit and tropical fruit, with gooseberry undertones. The palate is balanced, has a beautiful freshness and lengthy finish.

name: The Legendary Dark Non-Chill Filtered Irish Whiskey
description:
Nose : Fresh apple and pear with spiced dry smoke and welcoming virgin oak.

Taste : The Dark Silkie's signature softness develops to a rich salted caramel sweetness. Waves of sweet pipe tobacco, liquorice and dark chocolate give way to warm toffee and pear.

Finish : Warming elegant finish of malty smoke and peanut butter.

name: The Legendary Non-Chill Filtered Irish Whiskey
description:
Nose : Fresh with gentle malt, green apple opens up to a more honeyed butteryness.

Taste : Super soft, warm sweet honeyed ginger bread, hints of orange zest, brioche and butterscotch.

Finish : Warming elegant finish with the slightest hint of peat.

name: The Midnight Non-Chill Filtered Irish Whiskey
description:
Colour : Yellow Gold.

Nose : Rich muscovado sweetness, pipe smoke, christmas spice, sandalwood, orange zest, baked apples, chocolate orange, sweet tobacco, rounded, linseed and earthy.

Taste : Initially intense molasses sweetness, as it warms a dry peat smoke takes over. Pipe ash , raisins and sultanas boiled with nutmeg, cinnamon and cloves. Then toffee apples, a toasted, drying oak and tobacco and leather and yet a freshness – a brisk hint of pine and blood oranges even sweet grapefruit.

Finish : The sweet spice just melts gently way and leaves a comforting dried fruit and peat fire warmth.

name: Sauvignon Blanc Vin Blanc
description: Full of exotic fruit flavors combined with citrus and tropical fruits.

name: Cabernet Sauvignon California
description: Dark ruby in color, with aromas of black currants, anise, tobacco, and dark chocolate. On the palate the wine presents flavors of blackberries, cherries, cocoa and toasty oak, which are complemented by soft tannins that lead to a silky finish.

name: Petit Chablis
description: Young and crispy, with delicate floral and fruity aromas, this wine, light to medium-body, is lighter in style than a Chablis. It retains though the typical mineral characteristics of the area. The wine is vinified in vats to ensure that its freshness, minerality, floral aromas and fruity notes are secured. It is ready to drink young when it has already developed its charm and finesse.

name: London Dry Gin
description:
TASTING NOTES
The Nose: Floral, summer meadow notes, followed by mellow rounded juniper and zesty, citrus freshness.
The Palate: Dry juniper leads, then reveals lemon tart & orange marmalade, before all the flavours harmonise.
The Finish: Dryness leads, with spicy juniper & a hint of lemon tart emerging.

name: Chardonnay Uncovered
description: Lemon meringue, baking spice. A wine that is rooted to the earth. Rich. Focused. Refi ned.

name: Cabernet Sauvignon North Coast
description: Aromas of violets, blueberry and plum, clove/anise spices, coffee and chocolate. The wine fills the palate and lingers with chocolate and darker fruits meeting the bold tannins to linger.

name: Cabernet Sauvignon Spring Mountain District
description: Distinctive red and black currant and blueberry fruit with a lifted perfume of violets, mint, soy sauce and dried thyme. Full bodied with a grapey freshness and deeper dark flavors of mocha, red currant and asphalt. Rich with a silky texture, savory tannins and a long, cool finish.

name: Chardonnay North Coast
description: Beautiful aromas of honeysuckle with bright citrus notes of meyer lemon and mandarin orange followed by aromas of apricot and white peach, then subtle oak notes and an elegant acidity to lengthen the finish.

name: Pinot Noir Sonoma Coast

name: Red Blend North Coast
description: Aromas of cranberry and plum, warm baking spices, purple floral (violet) and chocolate. The full entry offers a round palate where the fruits, spices and tannins gracefully meet, extending into a lingering finish.

name: Cabernet Sauvignon California
description: Slow Press Cabernet Sauvignon undergoes malolactic fermentation and is then aged in American oak barrels for 9 months. This process delivers bold, concentrated flavors of dark fruits, blackberries and cassis, with notes of tobacco and leather. Its robust structure and firm tannins grip the taste buds, leaving a velvety finish.

name: Chardonnay Monterey County
description: Monterey County delivers a classic Chardonnay with a toasty finish. The Slow Press winemaking process magnifies fruit aromas and delivers notes of fresh apple, lemon, and pear. Slow Press Chardonnay is aged in American oak barrels for 9 months to develop a full-bodied, creamy mouthfeel.

name: Sauvignon Blanc Monterey County
description: This Monterey County Sauvignon Blanc is bursting with crisp, refreshing notes of citrus and passionfruit. It is sur lie aged to bring out the fullest flavors and a richer mouthfeel, and reveals a tropical, fruit-forward flavor profile.

name: Rosé of Pinot Noir Estate Cuvée Willamette Valley
description: Our Rosé of Pinot Noir presents with bright ruby red grapefruit on the nose and across the palate. Flavors of citrus, bergamot, and fresh tropical fruits intertwine with a crisp acidity. Lingering notes of golden raspberry give way to a smooth finish.

name: Durango Blanco Sotol 86 Proof
description: Distinctive aroma of hazelnut and almond. Notes of butter and yeast coming from the fermentation. Semi-sweet with a medium intensity. Slight minerality.

name: Dasylirion Cedrosanum
description: The La Higuera Cedrosanum Sotol has mineral and caramel notes on the nose. Smoked grass and cedar show on the palate. The finish is dry, and the texture has a near perfect balance.

name: Dasylirion Wheeleri

name: Utiel-Requena Tempranillo
description: Juicy, smooth and tangy with pure plum and racy raspberry, fresh and lively, balanced and certified Organic, quite charming.

name: Chardonnay
description: Chardonnay announces itself with a textbook Russian River Valley nose, dominated by a floral component and informed by honeysuckle and orange blossom. Fruit notes of nectarine and lemon oil, complexities of hazelnut, and a kiss of reduction tie all the components together into an aromatic assault with laser beam like focus. Once in the mouth, uber-suave textures hug the palate delivering a sizzling array of Chablis-inspired flavors—green apples, nectarines, citrus peel, dandelion—propped up with an undeniable minerality which provides fabulous energy through the long finish.

name: Pinot Noir 'Nichole's Blend'
description: A deep inky blue-purple color introduces this gorgeous wine. After a light swirl a mélange of ripe raspberry, Marion berry, streusel, sassafras, cedar, and sweet oak fill the glass. The potpourri of aromas is matched on the palate. Draped with suave tannins, sappy red fruit and sassafras are tied together with notes of blood orange. Lingering flavors of ripe raspberry and mocha coffee bring closure to an extremely pleasing wine.

name: Pinot Noir Umino Vineyard Russian River Valley
description: An inky purple color introduces this impressive wine. Intense aromas of roasted grains, ripe summer blackberries, vanilla crème, and violets fill the bowl. Dense flavors of ripe blackberries are highlighted by hints of roasted coffee and chocolate. The finish possesses youthful, silky tannins that dance gracefully with blue fruit and umami flavors.

name: Pinot Noir Weir Vineyard
description: The wines from the Weir vineyard continue to impress this winemaker. This complex wine possesses aromas of cherry cola, black cherry, espresso, Herbs de Provence, and rose blossoms. Seamless mid-weight flavors of cola, cocoa nib, and ripe red fruits coat the palette.

name: Rosé
description: A rich pink color introduces aromas of white strawberry, watermelon rind, ginger and peach pit which are accompanied by smoky, minerality elements. Refreshing flavors of fresh spring strawberries, honeydew melon and raspberries spread across the tongue and lead into a smooth, lingering finish.

name: Rosé
description: A rich pink color introduces aromas of white strawberry, watermelon rind, ginger and peach pit which are accompanied by smoky, minerality elements. Refreshing flavors of fresh spring strawberries, honeydew melon and raspberries spread across the tongue and lead into a smooth, lingering finish.

name: Cabernet Sauvignon California
description:
This wine showcases lush texture and bold dark fruit
flavors of blackberry, ripe purple plum and cassis with
a hint of oak and spice. Cedar and tobacco aromas accent the full, round palate, and the wine finishes with soft, integrated tannins.

name: Chardonnay California
description:
This wine features bright and lush tropical fruit flavors
like pineapple, banana, guava, and kiwi. These bright flavors are balanced with notes of vanilla and classic créme brulee.

name: Merlot California
description:
This approachable wine, has deep flavors of ripe berry
and balanced American oak. It was created to demonstrate the dark yet playful profile of Merlot with its soft tannins and rich aromatics of mixed berry pie,
cocoa, cigar box and decadent leather.

name: Petite Sirah California
description:
This wine has an intense color and generous bouquet of rich blackberries and  blueberries, vanilla bean  and roasted coffee all in a remarkably approachable glass. The wine is crafted to unleash dark and luscious 
characteristics, while managing tannins to deliver an opulent and juicy Petite Sirah.

name: Pinot Noir California
description: Spellbound Pinot Noir has an alluring color and inviting bouquet of rich raspberries, cherries and red currant, vanilla bean and roasted coffee, all in a remarkably approachable glass. The wine is crafted to unleash dark and luscious characteristics, while managing tannins to deliver an opulent and juicy Pinot Noir.

name: Jalisco 55 Non-Alcoholic Tequila Cocktail
description: The finished product is an elegant and herbaceous reposado spirit - minus the burn of alcohol. Sniff, and you'll catch a whiff of sweet agave, zesty citrus, fresh sweet mint, and just a touch of cinnamon. Sip, and you'll taste hints of honey, spicy oak, vanilla, and delicate pepper.

name: Kentucky 74 Non-Alcoholic Bourbon Cocktail
description: Kentucky 74 delivers a high-quality, smooth finish, underpinned by familiar notes of caramel, vanilla, and oak.

name: Kentucky 74 Non-Alcoholic Bourbon Cocktail
description: Kentucky 74 delivers a high-quality, smooth finish, underpinned by familiar notes of caramel, vanilla, and oak.

name: Kentucky 74 Spiced Non-Alcoholic Cinnamon Whiskey Cocktail
description: Kentucky 74 SPICED is basically sweater weather in a shot glass. The vanilla and baking spices will remind you of fresh-baked apple pie, while deep, woodsy cinnamon lends a little extra bite.

name: Old Fashioned Non-Alcoholic Cocktail
description: Kentucky 74, cane sugar, Chai, orange.

name: Whiskey Sour Non-alcoholic Cocktail
description: Non-alcoholic bourbon, add a touch of cane sugar for sweetness and then pucker up to a bit of fresh lemon. The result is a zero-proof, ready-to-drink masterpiece for even the most sophisticated whiskey connoisseur.

name: Pinot Grigio
description: Convivial flavors of bright citrus, light floral and melon move effortlessly into a lingering finish for a wine that is crisp, dry and versatile.

name: Hop Rising Double IPA
description: A mighty hop-lover’s dream, Hop Rising adds malty backbone to an intense Imperial IPA. This insanely smooth, dry-hopped ale has everything.

name: Hop Rising Double IPA
description: A mighty hop-lover’s dream, Hop Rising adds malty backbone to an intense Imperial IPA. This insanely smooth, dry-hopped ale has everything.

name: Signature French Brandy
description: St-Rémy from France, provided by Remy Cointreau Usa, Inc. Enjoy the unique taste and quality.

name: VSOP Brandy
description:
St-Rémy VSOP embodies the iconic and historical taste of St-Rémy.
It is a translation of the original recipe that made St-Rémy renowned around the Globe.

The right choice for a great authentic taste.
St-Rémy VSOP conveys the taste of small, freshly-picked red berries, while bringing out the sweet vanilla flavor of oak. It is a round, balanced spirit that is easy to drink. With its light and subtle nose,

St-Rémy VSOP is excellent neat, on ice or with a simple mixer.

St-Rémy XO is a brandy of character with complex aromas and a robust taste.
It is recognized for its elegance, roundness and ability to linger on the palate.

Offering multiple layers of flavors that make it remarkable to critics and
connoisseurs alike, St-Rémy XO can be enjoyed neat, on ice or in classic cocktails.

name: Riesling
description: This Riesling has crisp, sweet aromas and flavors of green apples, limes and passion fruit. The grapes are from the Mosel-Saar-Ruwer region of Germany. The steep south facing slopes and stony slate soils are ideal growing conditions for Riesling. Due to the steep slopes the vines are trained up 8 foot high wooden stakes and are harvested by hand.

name: Elderflower Liqueur
description: A fruity aroma with the sweetness and flavor of tropical fruits, grapefruit and pear.

name: Cabernet Sauvignon Paso Robles
description: Standing Goat from United States, provided by United States Distilled Prod. Enjoy the unique taste and quality.

name: Sauvignon Blanc
description: Starborough Sauvignon Blanc has layers of citrus and tropical fruit with hints of fresh green characters, which make the wine a true expression of the Marlborough region. Flavors of passion fruit, guava and kiwi layered over a citrus framework culminate in a crisp, approachable palate.

name: Sauvignon Blanc
description: Starborough Sauvignon Blanc has layers of citrus and tropical fruit with hints of fresh green characters, which make the wine a true expression of the Marlborough region. Flavors of passion fruit, guava and kiwi layered over a citrus framework culminate in a crisp, approachable palate.

name: Starlite Sauvignon Blanc Marlborough
description: Bright and flavorful. Each sip is full of mouthwatering notes of tropical citrus and fresh lemongrass.

name: Gewürztraminer
description: Starling Castle gets its name from the flocks of birds which surround the vineyards during each harvest, hoping to catch some of the delicious ripe grapes. The beautiful, sweeping vineyards of the Pfalz region produce one of Germany's most distinctive wines, Gewiirztraminer. This pleasantly aromatic, medium-sweet Gewiirztraminer captures delightful flavors of pear, sweet oranges and cinnamon. A perfect companion to soft cheeses, spicy cuisine, or simply enjoy on its own.

name: Glühwein
description: This sweet holiday classic is jam packed with savory winter spices including cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg with a hint of orange zest. It pairs well with holiday cheer and is best enjoyed warm in the company of good friends.

name: Rheinhessen Riesling
description: Starling Castle gets its name from the flocks of starling birds which surround the vineyards during each harvest, hoping to catch some of the ripe golden-green Riesling grapes. The Rheinhessen valley, with gently rolling hills, produces Germany's most famous wine, Riesling. This elegant, well balanced Riesling with its fresh, fruity bouquet is the perfect companion to light meals, desserts, or simply enjoy on its own.

name: Calabria Arvino
description: Ruby red color with purple highlights. Intense and complex bouquet on the nose with aromas of dried fruit and flowers, cloves, spices, tobacco and mocha. Elegant, full-flavored sip, with a good body, smooth polished tannins and a long finish.

name: Calabria Gaglioppo
description:
Color : Ruby red.
Bouquet : Intense aromas of cherry and spices on the nose, together with more delicate scents of violet, pomegranate and ripe plum.
Flavor : On the palate it shows a pleasant and elegant personality, with a good structure, perfectly balanced between freshness and smoothness.

name: Calabria Greco
description: Statti from Italy, provided by Vias Imports. Enjoy the unique taste and quality.

name: Cabernet Sauvignon Bourbon Barrel Aged California
description:
The result is a refined, full-bodied Cabernet with bold fruit flavors. Dark cherry, blackberry and plum enrich the palate, providing excellent structure and generous tannins.

The bourbon influences add notes of vanilla, caramel, and spice that lead into a long, smooth finish.

name: Chardonnay California
description: Stephen Vincent from United States, provided by Wine Hooligans. Enjoy the unique taste and quality.

name: Pinot Noir California
description: Stephen Vincent from United States, provided by Wine Hooligans. Enjoy the unique taste and quality.

name: Margarita
description: Cloudy yellow straw green color. Aromas of sliced pepper, squash, lime rind, and peanut have carrot cake like quality with a tangy sweet medium body and a candied yams, brown sugar, and lime sorbet finish. A bit funky (in a good way) on the nose, but quite tasty on the palate.

name: Bloody Mary Rimmer
description: The ultimate Bloody Mary needs the ultimate Bloody Mary Rim salt to go with all those tasty garnishes. Our easy salt rimmer is packed with wholesome sea salt, sugar crystals and the key-ingredient:  tomato powder for that big tomato taste.

name: Pomegranate Liqueur
description: This expertly crafted pomegranate liqueur is infused with the ripe red brambly flavor of pomegranates and the natural aroma of fresh berry jam.

name: Simple Blood Orange Martini Cocktail Mix
description: Sweet like strawberry. Tart like citrus. Stirrings Blood Orange Cocktail Mix elevates ordinary cocktails and turns them into a firework display for the senses. Distinctive and out-of-the-ordinary, this mixer is an easy way to take cocktails like cosmos, daiquiris and mimosas to a higher level of wow.

name: Simple Dirty Martini
description: Classic cocktails are always in style with Stirrings, we make crafting a Dirty Martini easy with our Dirty Martini mixer that uses imported olive brine, filtered water, and just the right amount of salt. This mixer is an olive lover’s delight. With Stirrings olive brine recipe, you choose how light or how dirty you want your martini.

name: Simple Pomegranate Martini Cocktail Mix
description: The pomegranate has been an object of mysticism throughout the ages. With its delicious plump seeds and remarkable health benefits, we took great care developing our Pomegranate Cocktail Mix. It is an inspired, sweet-tart blend of pomegranate, lemon juice and cane sugar. Try it Bellini style, with sparkling wine, or with sparkling water for a Pomegranate Spritzer.

name: Simple Syrup
description: Simple Syrup is the perfect starting point for many great cocktails and a mandatory bottle to have in any well-stocked bar. Ours contains only pure cane sugar and triple-filtered water for a staple that takes the guesswork out of making cocktails that need a dollop of sweet. So easy to use it’s hard to imagine living without once you’ve created the perfect Daiquiri or Gin Rickey.

name: Triple Sec Liqueur
description: This expertly crafted Triple Sec Liqueur is infused with a natural fresh aroma and flavor of juicy sweet valencia oranges. Stirrings liqueurs better ingredients make simply better cocktails.

name: The Original Premium Vodka 80 Proof
description: Stoli® Vodka is a classically styled, exceptionally smooth vodka. Crystal clear in color with marshmallow, mineral and mild fruit peel aromas, a soft, supple entry leads to a smooth, medium bodied palate with pastry frosting, talc and citrus rind flavors. It finishes with a clean, lightly sweet, sugar dust, wet straw and balanced pepper fade.

name: Chardonnay Dundee Hills
description: Our Dundee Hills Chardonnay, sourced entirely of estate fruit, is fermented and aged in stainless steel tanks to capture the fresh, crisp fruit of the variety. It shows aromas of chamomile and lychee with hints of lemon rind. On the palate, flavors of pear and tropical fruits are balanced by its acidity.

name: Pinot Gris Swing
description: The wine opens with a bright note of lemon peel and tangerine. The palate is zippy and refreshing, begging for a “cheers” to another quenching sip.

name: Pinot Noir Dundee Hills
description:
Crafted exclusively from estate fruit, our Dundee Hills Pinot Noir is made in an elegant, approachable style. It has aromas of brambleberry and cherry with floral notes of lilac and violets and understated hints of cola and cinnamon. The palate
features a purity of red fruit flavors, bright acidity and medium tannins.

name: Pinot Noir Reserve Dundee Hills
description:
Our Reserve Pinot Noir comes from a selection of our best vineyard blocks and barrels in the cellar. It is barrel aged in French oak for 10 months prior to bottling and carefully blended from individual lots to articulate the vintage. The
palate displays an integrated balance of dark cherry and raspberry, accented by spicy notes on its seamless finish.

name: Pinot Noir Rosé Dundee Hills
description:
WINE OVERVIEW
Pinot Noir Rosé has been a cornerstone of our
production for more than a decade. Comprised of
various clones of Pinot Noir, we intentionally craft our
Rosé to be balanced and bright.
Whole cluster pressed and fermented in stainless steel,
our 2019 Willamette Valley Pinot Noir Rosé shows
alluring aromatics of ruby red grapefruit and stone
fruits. The palate displays flavors of watermelon and
strawberry lemonade with mouthwatering acidity. The
lingering notes of minerality on the finish will draw you
back for another sip.
HARVEST OVERVIEW
The 2019 vintage was a return to a classic Oregon
growing season. Bud break, bloom, lag phase, and
harvest dates all fell within days of the 2013 and 2014
vintages. Our estate crop set on target with expected
levels for all varieties. Moderate summer weather
persisted, presenting very few heat spikes and delivering
only one notable record-breaking day in June. Cool, wet
weather arrived early in September, pushing ripening
and delaying the harvest window. The conditions in
late September and October returned to sunny days
and brisk nights, allowing us to pick based on ripe fruit
flavors and near-perfect natural acidity.

name: Pinot Noir Swing
description: Stoller Family Estate from United States, provided by Stoller Family Estate. Enjoy the unique taste and quality.

name: Pinot Noir Willamette Valley
description: A mosaic of Pinot Noir from our estate, this  wines is a mix of all our Pinot Noir clones. It saw mostly whole berry, and primarily native yeast fermentation before aging primarily in neutral French oak for almost a year. Notes of dark  red fruit, cola, and earth are met with layers of complexity — a classic representation of the Dundee Hills.

name: Swing Bubbles
description: You’re greeted with a light, citrus-packed nose, bountiful with lemon zest and lime. The palate is delightfully refreshing, leading to a clean, crisp finish.

name: Swing Rosé Bubbles
description: The nose welcomes you with lemon rind and strawberry. Bubbly and playful notes of raspberry lemonade and lime zest grace the palate.

name: Swing Rosé Spritz
description: A light, refreshing rosé spritz made from hand-selected Pinot Noir blended with local vermouth, natural flavors, and botanicals that’s ever so slightly sweetened and bottled with a kiss of effervescence. Vibrant notes of grapefruit and cara cara orange lead to a mélange of ginger and lemon zest on the palate that and unwinds to a crisp citrus finish.

name: Swing Rosé Spritz
description: A light, refreshing rosé spritz made from hand-selected Pinot Noir blended with local vermouth, natural flavors, and botanicals that’s ever so slightly sweetened and bottled with a kiss of effervescence. Vibrant notes of grapefruit and cara cara orange lead to a mélange of ginger and lemon zest on the palate that and unwinds to a crisp citrus finish.

name: Swing White Blend
description: This vibrant wine opens with scents of white flowers and citrus. Its buoyant vibrancy lifts the palate to highlight flavors of lime zest and fresh melon. Perfect for a day at the beach or hitting the links.

name: Cabernet Sauvignon Hawke's Bay
description:
Nose : Ripe aromas of blackberry, cocoa powder, cardamom, vanilla, and cedar notes from the oak.

Palate : Plush and velvety and shows dark fruits dominated by blackberry and a hint of mocha, supported by fleshy tannins.

name: Sauvignon Blanc Hawke's Bay
description:
Nose : Tropical flavors of guava and lychee, green melon with notes of lemon grass and grapefruit.

Palate : Refreshing with lively passionfruit fruit flavors, a plush mid palate, and crisp grapefruit citrus finish.

name: Sauvignon Blanc Marlborough
description:
Aroma And Palate : This wine displays vibrant and punchy aromatics of grapefruit, white peach and passionfruit with a scattering of tropical stone fruits.

This wine demonstrates mouth-watering acidity, and minerality. A lovely young and dynamic drop that finishes with a pleasing fresh passionfruit note that lingers.

name: Cabernet Sauvignon Alexander Valley
description: Stonestreet Estate Vineyards from United States, provided by Jackson Family Wines. Enjoy the unique taste and quality.

description: Our rich, bold Cabernet Sauvignon is comprised of grapes grown from some of California’s most storied vineyards. Layers of delicious flavor from each region integrate with notes of nutmeg and vanilla for a complex Cabernet Sauvignon.

name: Colorado Whiskey
description:
Nose : caramel-butterscotch, vanilla, maple syrup, leather.

Palate : cinnamon-butter, vanilla, chocolate, warm caramel & spiced pear; flows over the tongue like table cream & melted brown sugar, finishing with a hint of cayenne, rich tobacco, oak & aged leather.

name: Diamond Peak Colorado Whiskey
description:
Stranahan’s Diamond Peak is aged in  #3 char New White American Oak barrels. 

Nose : Dried apricot, tack-shed leather, black licorice, hint of wet cedar.

Palate : Turkish apricot, dark-roast coffee, butterscotch oak, cayenne and Mexican hot chocolate, with the parting gift of a rolling, creamy finish.

name: Rocky Mountain Blue Peak Colorado Single Malt Whiskey
description:
Blue Peak is an American single malt distilled at high altitude, aged in new American oak barrels, and Solera finished, a maturation process typically used in wine, resulting in a rich and mellow whiskey.

Named for a 13-thousand-foot peak in Aspen and inspired by the alpine scenery of the Rocky Mountains, Blue Peak is built around a small batch of single malt whiskey that has been hand-crafted at a high altitude and aged for 4 years in 53-gallon, new American oak barrels with a #3 char, imbuing a warm, toasted flavor.

The profile of the aged expression is expanded through the time-honored Solera process, accentuating the liquid with fruit and butterscotch characteristics.

name: Rocky Mountain Sherry Cask Single Malt Whiskey
description:
Our Oloroso Sherry barrels are procured from the Andalusia region of southwestern Spain, known to many oenophiles as the Sherry Triangle and one of the world’s most coveted wine regions. The barrels have aged sherry wine for over 40 years, leaving behind a depth of flavor soaked into the ancient oak staves. The resulting whiskey bursts with rich flavors of vanilla, caramel, dark chocolate and oak. The use of sherry casks in cask finishing has been a popular practice throughout Europe for centuries and Stranahan’s Sherry Cask is an American approach to this tradition.

Nose : Over-ripe cherry, sweet apples, raisins, almonds, leather and fresh-cut hay.

Palate : Honey, Montmorency cherries, blackcurrant, and fig, with a nutty brine and walnut characteristics.

Finish : Buttery caramel, whipped creme, brown sugar and smoked cayenne.

name: Cabernet Sauvignon Cs Columbia Valley

Tasting Notes by Winemaker Charles Smith
Cabernet Sauvignon elixir. Blackberry, currant, pencil lead, cedar. Layered and deep, resting in the glass, inviting you to sip
and sip. Rich, complex, and just plain delicious – the best vintage to date.

name: Cabernet Sauvignon Cs Elemental Columbia Valley (On Premise Only)
description: Truly amazing. Deep blue and black in color. Mouth-filling layers of black currant, blackberry, cedar box and crushed stone. Death-defying balance and a firm, rich finish that seems to never end. Yes, amazing. –Winemaker Charles Smith

name: Chardonnay Ch Columbia Valley
description:
Tasting Notes by Winemaker Charles Smith
Cool Liquid Sunshine. Mouth-filling tangerine, Meyer lemon curd and a kiss of butterscotch. Silky and rich to the last long sip!

name: Pinot Noir Pn Columbia Valley

Tasting Notes by Winemaker Charles Smith
Fairy dust minerality lifts from the glass, cloaked in wild strawberry, hibiscus, and oyster mushroom, as a lavish palate of
rose petal, red cherry, orange zest and potting soil set this elegant table. Fresh, expansive, and long – pure Pinot magic!

name: Rb Red Blend Columbia Valley
description: Substance from United States, provided by K Vintners. Enjoy the unique taste and quality.

name: Sauvignon Blanc Sb Columbia Valley

Tasting Notes by Winemaker Charles Smith
Hold on tight and open your mouth to the launch of this explosive and captivating beauty. Grapefruit, fresh cut grass, lemon grass
and flint start you on the journey of discovery followed by an outburst of fresh pine needles, mountain wildflowers and lime leaf.
Crisp, focused, and very long. Enjoy the ride!

name: Vineyard Collection Cabernet Sauvignon CS Powerline Estate Vineyard Walla Walla Valley
description:
Tasting Notes by Winemaker Charles Smith
Powerline delivers again with black current, cigar wrapper, forest floor, and mint. Undeniable, vivacious, and fantastic. Black plum,
crushed rock, anise, and bay leaf. Clear, refined, and completely Cabernet.

name: Vineyard Collection Cabernet Sauvignon CS Powerline Estate Vineyard Walla Walla Valley

description: Another classic to behold! Broken limestone and honeycomb enrich the senses, followed more subtly with verbena, grapefruit rind, white peach and green apple. Zippy, long, and rich, finishing with sea spray, lemon zest and a lovely perfume.

name: Bubbly Rosé Central Coast
description: Ideal for drinking year-round, Summer Water Bubbly is refreshing and light with just a hint of sweetness, and showcases notes of candied strawberry, melon, and fragrant white flowers like elderflower. Bubbly and fun, this bottle promises to enhance all of your celebratory activities.

name: Rosé Central Coast
description: Summer never ends with Summer Water Rosé. This perennial favorite is delightfully crisp, lighthearted, and destined for a good time. The grapes for this wine were picked early in the season to achieve a natural acidity that’s ideal for warm-weather drinking. To ensure as little extraction from the skins as possible, we used the direct press method, retaining the delicate fruit aromas and pale color rosé is known for. The result is light, aromatic, and dry - with notes of grapefruit, peach, rose, and peach. Summer-friendly fare like shellfish, ceviche, and salads will pair swimmingly or just drink it chilled with the ones you love.

name: Vodka 80 Proof
description: SVEDKA Vodka is a smooth-drinking vodka infused with a subtle, rounded sweetness, making it an ideal addition to countless vodka cocktails. Now made in the USA, this unflavored vodka is distilled four times to remove impurities, using a continuous distillation process to ensure that ingredients never stall or pool. The result is a clean, clear taste with a balanced body and a crisp finish, making this 80 proof vodka a bold, crowd-pleasing choice. Mix this popular vodka alcohol into cosmopolitans or vodka martinis, or chill this 750 mL vodka bottle and pour over ice to enjoy a vodka on the rocks, savoring the crisp finish.

name: Hi-Falutin' Whipper Snapper Oregon Blended Whiskey 84 Proof
description: WhipperSnapper opens with warm, toasty notes of hazelnut and rye loaf, underpinned by creamy malt aromas. The palate is lively and giving, with a deft balance between aromatics of grain and barrel. Notes of crystal malt, demerara sugar, and sweet earth abound. WhipperSnapper finishes with an elegant flourish of viscosity, with vibrant, expressive notes of rye and malt.

name: Old Tom Gin 88 Proof
description: Ransom Old Tom Gin opens with seductive aromatics of juniper berries and coastal forest, set off by apothecary spice notes of cardamom and angelica. The palate is rich and silky, with malt flavors punctuated by lively citrus zest and heady exotic notes of coriander and teak. The gin continues with suppleness and power, with the warmth and richness of the malt carrying clean, focused botanicals on a long, elegant finish.

name: Rye Barley Wheat Whiskey 93.4 Proof
description: Rich aromatics of hazelnut shortbread and sugar cookie provide an approachable counterbalance to earthy spice notes from the rye. On the palate, a smooth entry with flavors of Amoroso sherry and brown butter continues to build in breadth and viscosity. The finish is lush and enduring, with sweet honey notes and a polished hint of baking spices.

name: The Emerald 1865 Straight American Whiskey

description: What makes Takara Mirin such an essentail ingredient for cooking is its unique combination of three key components - alcohol, amino acids, and sugar - and their synergetic effects in cooking. Takara Mirin is made with premium sake, rich in natural amino acids, containing alcohol and additional natural sweetners.

description: KISSUI is made from the finest rice and the purist spring water in Japan. An exceptional distilling process, called “Super-Allospas,” distinguishes the pristine spirit from any other. Smooth and elegant, this well-polished vodka pleases the palate from the first sip to the silky finish. KISSUI enchants, whether on the rocks or paired with your favorite mix.

description: Tanduay from Philippines, provided by Mhw Ltd/midway Trading. Enjoy the unique taste and quality.

name: Dark Rum
description:
Color : Dark amber color.

Nose : Amaretti cookies.

Taste : Butterscotch, frozen custard, cola, caramel apple.

Body : Candied & Mild.

Finish : Smooth caramel, tropical fruits finish.

name: Gold Asian Rum
description:
Color : Bright, golden amber.

Nose : Refined and elegant. Presence of mature honey, almond, caramel, toasted oak, orange peels and vanilla.

Taste : Good balance of alcohol level and sweetness. Expressive flavors of vanilla, tropical fruit, coconut and nutmeg.

Body : Mellow, smooth and dry.

Finish : Persistent in harmony. Caramel flavor persist on the finish, with vanilla and wooden notes.

name: Silver Asian Rum 80 Proof
description:
Color : Clear, transparent, pale-straw yellow.

Nose : Good intensity of mandarin and grapefruit peel with toasted notes, coconut and vanilla background.

Taste : Cream soda with flavors of citrus fruits all in harmony.

Body : Satiny, crisp, fruity light to medium body.

Finish : Dry yet sweet with warm persistence.

name: White Rum
description:
Color : Clear, colorless.

Nose : Raw coconut, spritz of lime, white pepper, and cumin.

Taste : A light simple taste of sweet cream and pepper.

Body : Fresh mild body.

Finish : Light sweetness with smooth citrus rind and peppery finish.

name: London Dry Gin
description:
Fortune favours the brave. Back in the 1830´s Charles Tanqueray wasn't afraid to mix his bold ideas. His ingenious pursuit for perfection paid off, creating Tanqueray London Dry, a perfectly balanced gin and one of the most awarded gins in the world.

The bartender´s choice for the perfect G&T. Best enjoyed with tonic and a wedge of lime.

name: Nº Ten Gin
description:
Furthering the legacy of the original London Dry recipe, Tanqueray No.10 sets the standard as the first ultra-premium gin. Distilled in small batches with the four original botanicals of London Dry and the addition of fresh whole grapefruits, oranges, limes and chamomile flowers, Tanqueray No. 10 Gin brings an explosion of fresh citrus with every sip. Tanqueray No.10 is the only Gin and only white spirit that has been awarded a place in the Hall of Fame at the San Francisco Spirits Awards, an honour we are exceptionally proud of. The smooth & delicious taste of Tanqueray No.10 Gin makes it the unmistakable premium gin of the Tanqueray range.

Tanqueray No.10 Gin is best enjoyed with plenty of ice, tonic water and garnished with a wedge of pink grapefruit.

Aroma : Passionfruit, gooseberry, green capsicum.

Palate : Passionfruit, lemon, grapefruit, zingy acid.

name: Valencia Tempranillo Crianza
description: Aromas of ripe sour cherries, balsam, herbal notes, fresh pipe tobacco, dill, while the palate displays classic notes of vanilla cherry cola, cedar, cypress, leather, and baking spice. Exhibits silky, integrated tannins balanced with prominent acidity, medium-plus body.

name: 4 Years Old Bottled-In-Bond High-Rye Bourbon Whishkey
description: Hearty notes of maple on the nose, the palate starts dry with notes of black pepper, graham cracker, and dried fruit.

name: 4 Years Old Bottled-In-Bond Wheated Bourbon Whiskey
description: Toasted marshmallow on the nose, the palate starts with a touch of sweetness heightened by flavors of caramel, vanilla, and stone fruit.

name: 4 Years Old Interstate American Single Malt Whiskey
description: Inspired by the first interstate park in the nation, Tattersall Interstate American Single-Malt Whiskey is distilled from a blend of malted barley, cherrywood-smoked barley and dark roasted barley. After aging at least four years in virgin oak barrels, the result is a complex sipper with rich notes of chocolate and cherry with a hint of coffee.

name: 5 Years Aged Straight Rye Whiskey
description: Tattersall Distilling Company from United States, provided by Tattersall LLC. Enjoy the unique taste and quality.

name: Absinthe Blanche
description:
Full-bodied and wonderful.

Tattersall Absinthe is a gorgeous balance of the Holy Trinity 
anise, wormwood and fennel. Prepare for complex sensations with every sip.

Full-bodied, rich, sweet, bitter and herbal at the same time.

name: Aged 3 Years Single Barrel Kernza Whiskey
description: Tattersall Distilling Company from United States, provided by Tattersall LLC. Enjoy the unique taste and quality.

name: Amaro Bitter Liqueur
description:
The perfect after-dinner drink.

Tattersall Amaro is crafted from bitter roots and barks, and finished with macerated citrus. Its rich aroma and stimulating taste will engage all your senses.

Deep, bittersweet and earthy with a smooth spice finish.

name: Americano Liqueur
description:
Spicy, soft and brimming with flavor.

Tattersall Americano is a wine-based liqueur made from fermented and distilled grapes, infused with a distinct blend of botanicals. Enjoy it on the rocks or any cocktail that calls for dry vermouth.

Floral and slightly bitter with notes of lemon and bright herbs.

name: Aquavit
description:
The Scandinavian rival to our gin.

Tattersall Aquavit is crafted from a complex blend of botanicals with caraway leading the charge. Use it as a substitute for vodka to enjoy a new twist on the classics.

Caraway-forward with warm citrus and fennel notes.

name: Barreled Gin
description:
So compelling. It begs to be sipped neat.

Tattersall Barreled Gin is our flagship conditioned in French oak white wine barrels for an added layer of complexity. Try it on its own, you won’t regret it.

Distilled from 100% Certified Organic Corn Neutral Grain Spirits.

Subtle oak and fruit enhance the gin with soft floral notes reminiscent of dry vermouth in a martini.

name: Barreled Rum
description: Subtle oak and fruit enhance the gin with soft floral notes reminiscent of dry vermouth in a martini.

name: Barreled Rum
description: Subtle oak and fruit enhance the gin with soft floral notes reminiscent of dry vermouth in a martini.

name: Basil + Lemon Blueberry Collins
description: Tattersall Distilling Company from United States, provided by Tattersall LLC. Enjoy the unique taste and quality.

name: Birkie WI-SKI Straight Rye Whiskey
description: Tattersall Distilling Company from United States, provided by Tattersall LLC. Enjoy the unique taste and quality.

name: Bitter Orange Liqueur
description:
Bright citrus meets earthy botanicals.

Tattersall Bitter Orange is a complex liqueur crafted from a distinct blend of three different types of orange and an array of spices. You’ll love it in a Negroni, boulevadier or an Americano.

Bright orange notes at the start are backed with a warm, bitter bite.

name: Blueberry Liqueur
description:
Subtle, sweet and delicately delicious.

Tattersall Blueberry Liqueur is crafted from Great Lakes blueberries and an array of natural botanicals. Add it to your next gin and tonic, mix it with lemonade or add a sweet twist to your favorites.

Lemon citrus and lavender flavors balance with notes of thyme and tarragon.

name: Corpse Reviver #2
description: Made with Tattersall Gin, liquers and a touch of citrus, this fresh take on the idonic cocktail. Tart notes of orange and lemon mix with aromatic anise and wormwood for a refreshing sipper.

name: Cranberry Liqueur
description:
The perfect mix of sweet, sour and tart.

Made from Great Lakes cranberries and a mix of natural botanicals that enhance the berries, Tattersall Cranberry is a unique companion to your favorite spirits. Add a splash to your cosmopolitan, mix with a hard cider or top off your gin and tonic.

Sweet, sour and tart, balanced by an herbal finish.

name: Crème De Fleur Floral Liqueur
description:
A balancing act of six aromatic flowers.

Tattersall Crème de Fleur is distilled with six flowers and
post-macerated with additional flowers for a beautifully concentrated flavor and aroma.

Floral, sweet and perfectly balanced.

name: Fernet Liqueur
description:
Cleanses and awakens your senses like no other.

The product of more than 30 botanicals, spices and herbs,
Tattersall Fernet is an intensely complex liqueur that will pique your curiosity.

Unlike any other liqueur, its flavor and sensation engages every corner of your palate.

name: Gin
description:
A New World gin born from Old World wisdom.

Crafted with 22 carefully selected botanicals from around the globe, Tattersall Gin is our flagship for a reason — smooth and textured with just the right bite.

Distilled from 100% Certified Organic Corn Neutral Grain Spirits.

Citrus aromas complement a captivating balance of juniper, earth, and spice.

name: Grapefruit Crema Liqueur
description:
Bold, fresh and beautiful.

Made with a careful balance of flowers and grapefruit zest,
Tattersall Grapefruit Crema bursts with flavor unlike any other. Use in place of triple sec or Curaçao for a delicious twist.

Grapefruit Crema Liqueur.

name: Habanero Hand-Crafted Bitters
description: Tattersall Habanero Bitters are crafted from a distinct blend of carefully-selected herbs, spices and peppers. Spice up your margarita, mule or another favorite cocktail with just a few drops.

name: Italiano Liqueur
description:
Warm, spicy and just the right amount of bitterness.

Tattersall Italiano Style is a wine-based liqueur made from fermented and distilled grapes, infused with a distinct blend of botanicals. You can sip it on the rocks, in a Manhattan or any drink that calls for sweet vermouth.

Sweet and herbal with notes of orange, vanilla and cocoa.

name: Key Lime Flavored Gin + Tonic
description: Tattersall Distilling Company from United States, provided by Tattersall LLC. Enjoy the unique taste and quality.

name: Lime Crema Liqueur
description:
Beyond a splash of lime. 

Made from a distinct blend of lime, citrus and botanicals, Tattersall Lime Crema is a lively addition to your liqueur lineup. Add a robust citrus kick to the classics or simply mix with soda water.

Intense lime notes balance a refreshing aroma and subtle spice backbone.

name: Manhattan
description: Our 100% rye whiskey lends a peppery backbone with notes of toffee and maple. Whiskey is aged no less than two years and mellowed with a dash of our herbal Italiano Liqueur (reminiscent of sweet vermouth), sherry (which lends a nutty flavor), and aromatic bitters. Baking spice on the nose and perfectly balanced and round on the palate with minimal sweetness.

name: Manhattan
description: Our 100% rye whiskey lends a peppery backbone with notes of toffee and maple. Whiskey is aged no less than two years and mellowed with a dash of our herbal Italiano Liqueur (reminiscent of sweet vermouth), sherry (which lends a nutty flavor), and aromatic bitters. Baking spice on the nose and perfectly balanced and round on the palate with minimal sweetness.

name: Old Fashioned
description: Our 100% rye whiskey lends a peppery backbone with notes of toffee and maple, mellowed with a dash of orange zest, sour cherry liqueur, and aromatic bitters. Citrus and baking spice on the nose, and perfectly balanced and round on the palate.

name: Old Fashioned

description:
Not too sweet. Not too sour.

Tattersall Sour Cherry is the crafted with Montmorency cherries and aged in American oak barrels to create the perfect marriage of sweet and sour.

Intense taste of Montmorency cherries complemented by American oak.

name: Straight Rye Whiskey
description:
Big, bold and spicy.

Tattersall Straight Rye Whiskey is a Monongahela-style whiskey distilled from 100% Minnesota rye, grown and harvested 50 miles north of the distillery in Cambridge, MN. Perfect for rye purists, it’s aged for at least two years in 30 and 53 gallon charred white oak, sourced and coopered in Minnesota. Think of it as Bourbon’s bolder cousin. Enjoy it neat or in classics like an Old Fashioned or Manhattan.

Aromas of vanilla, maple, and mellow oak. Robust and peppery on the palate with lingering notes of caramel.

name: Tightline Mildwestern Organic Vodka
description: Clean, crisp and powered by the sun. Distilled from 100% Midwestern corn, Tightline Organic Vodka is made to reflect the spirit of the great outdoors. Quite possibly the smoothest, most neutral organic vodka out there, it’s the perfect base for all your favorite vodka cocktails.

name: Tightline Mildwestern Organic Vodka
description: Clean, crisp and powered by the sun. Distilled from 100% Midwestern corn, Tightline Organic Vodka is made to reflect the spirit of the great outdoors. Quite possibly the smoothest, most neutral organic vodka out there, it’s the perfect base for all your favorite vodka cocktails.

name: Toasted Coconut Aquavit
description: Warm and complex with a tropical hint. Toasted coconut elevates pumpernickel rye on the palate with hints of citrus, oak, and baking spice.

name: Vodka
description:
Always small batch. Always triple filtered.

Tattersall Vodka is crafted grain to glass from Midwestern corn. Subtle and refined, it’s the perfect base for the classics. Distilled from Midwestern Corn.

Clean and crisp with a hint of sweetness.

name: Chablis

name: Red

description: Deep amber in hue, Taylor Cream Sherry is a full bodied dessert wine with a medley of sweet and nutty flavors.

description:
A soft, medium dry sherry with a mellow, nutty flavor and smooth finish. A fine companion to both hors d'oeuvers and desserts, it can also be savored by itself.

name: Cabernet Merlot South Eastern Australia
description: Plum, coffee, and licorice notes round out this spicy wine.

name: Chardonnay South Eastern Australia
description: Soft and fruity, with pleasant guava and apple flavors on a light frame.

name: Shiraz South Eastern Australia
description: Light and distinctive with spicy cherry and anise flavors, which echo nicely on a soft finish.

name: Concord Grape
description: This is a vibrant, fruity grape-tasting wine that is light on alcohol and big on fruit taste.

name: The Good Stuff 4 Year Old Rye Whiskey
description: An unmistakable rye whiskey, Templeton Rye is smooth and spicy with a clean finish.

name: Crème De Banane Liqueur
description:
Tasting Notes : Deep, rich caramelized notes of ripe bananas reminiscent of warm banana bread or the famous New Orleans dessert, Bananas Foster.

Process :  Perfectly ripened bananas are small-batch distilled to extract the rich banana flavor.

Source : The golden amber color, extracted from mature bananas, is completely natural.

name: Crème De Cacao À La Vanille
description: Off the charts sweetness and powdered cocoa on the nose. Followed by amazing cocoa andbutter at entry, midpalate is spot-on dark chocolate, but neither bitter nor semisweet, it’s a perfect balance.

name: Crème De Menthe Glaciale
description: Entry flavor is sweet and viscous to the touch but the minty flavor is genuine and intensely splendid. This should be the only Crème de Menthe that astute bartenders who care about their craft will want.

name: Crème De Moka Coffee Liqueur
description: Rich aromas of nutty, fresh roasted coffee that prime the palate for waves of flavor. A touch of sweetness up front that's quickly balanced with a whisper of roasted bitterness. which sits on the midpalate as layers of dark berries and floral tones wash everything down smooth. This is a coffee liqueur divine enough to drink on its own or in your favorite cocktail, and as satisfying as that early morning cup that gets you going.

name: Crème De Noyaux Liqueur
description: Its flavor offers a complex "marzipan" note with sweet cherry undercurrent of aroma and flavor with a slight touch of balancing bitterness on the finish.

name: Gran Classico Bitter Liqueur
description: Entry is all about the rhubarb upfront, then in midpalate the gentian dominates before the orange peel comes rushing back in the finish as well as a piny/resiny quality that makes the aftertaste smashingly delicious. Campari drinkers take note: the ultimate expression of Bitter.

name: Kina L'Aero d'Or Vin Apèritif Au Quinquina
description: Created in an "Alps-Provence" style, Tempus Fugit "Kina L'Avion D'Or" is produced by infusing white wine with Cinchona bark, orange peel, wormwood and other exotic spices. The result is a perfectly balanced aperitif with a deep golden hue, aromas of quince and fine marmalade, and a complex, mildly bitter flavor that leads to an elegant sweetness on the finish.

name: Liqueur De Violettes
description: This unique and rare liqueur is based on a mid-19th century French recipe and is made only in micro-batches. The protocol uses the finest French violets, traditionally hand-harvested in the sunny and historic Côte d’Azur, along the Mediterranean Sea, amongst the myriad of precious flowers cultivated in the region for the world’s finest perfumes. This elegant elixir has a lower sugar content than the heavier “crème”-style violet cordials, which more intensely highlights its delicate floral aromatics.

name: TEN HIGH BBN 4 Year Old
description: An old bottling of Ten High Kentucky Sour Mash Bourbon Whiskey. Production of the Hiram Walker-owned brand began at the end of prohibition in the 1930s.

name: Friuli Aquileia Pinot Grigio
description:
Colour: Bright pale straw-yellow. 
Bouquet: Fresh and youthful, with hints of acacia flowers and subtle spicy tones. 
Flavour: Appealingly full-flavored; very well-balanced and persistent.

name: Friuli Aquileia Sauvignon
description: It is a Sauvignon Blanc that, on the nose, reveals hints of Mediterranean broom and tropical fruits, made even more elegant by the floral caress of hawthorn. It has the finesse of a Loire wine combined with the warmth of the Mediterranean. Its aromatic style makes it ideal for bringing out the best in fish, seafood and vegetable-based dishes, but it is also an excellent accompaniment for ethnic cuisines. It is a “glocal” wine: one that contains the roots and spirit of Friuli - from which it comes - as well as an international flavour.

name: Prosecco Brut
description: Our Prosecco is attractive pale straw-yellow color with a lively, persistent perlage and a rich mousse. The bouquet is refined and elegant with beautiful mineral notes, elegant white flowers and stone fruits, enhanced by pleasing fruity notes. The palate is dry and pleasantly fruity with a fresh, aromatic note on the finish.

name: Sicilia Nero d'Avola
description: Tenuta Regaleali from Italy, provided by Sutter Home/Trinchero Family Est. Enjoy the unique taste and quality.

name: Terre Siciliane Nerello Mascalese Le Rosé
description: Tenuta Regaleali from Italy, provided by Sutter Home/Trinchero Family Est. Enjoy the unique taste and quality.

name: Prosecco Brut
description: Straw-yellow color with pale green glints. Exuberant foam characterized by minuscule bubbles. Fresh bouquet initially of acacia flowers which gives way to aromas redolent of white peach and rennet. In the mouth it is surprisingly cool and vigorous, lively with a creamy perlage of fruity notes that titillate the palate exquisitely

name: Prosecco Brut
description: Straw-yellow color with pale green glints. Exuberant foam characterized by minuscule bubbles. In the mouth it is surprisingly cool and vigorous, lively with a creamy perlage of fruity notes that titillate the palate exquisitely

name: Prosecco Rosé
description: Prosecco Rose’ is made with 85% Glera (aka prosecco) with a splash of Pinot Noir which gives its bright pale pink color and fresh red berry notes. Excellent as an aperitif, it is versatile and can be served during the whole meal with white meat, seafood and light fares. A delightful twist on the beloved Italian sparkling wine.

name: Venezia Pinot Grigio
description: A grape variety of French origin, here in Italy this has become the most famous vine all over the world: in the north-east territories (the regions of Veneto, Friuli and Trentino Alto Adige) it has found its ideal habitat and on completion of the white wine-making process, proposes unpretentious, full-bodied wines that easily accompany a wide range of dishes

name: Maremma Toscana Sangiovese
description: Its color is a bright ruby red. On the nose, it is clean and precise, with hints of morello cherries, wild berries and a moderate spiciness. On the palate it reveals a full and firm flavor, expressing all its intensity and elegance.

name: Maremma Toscana Vermentino
description: A bright straw yellow heralds the intense, elegant bouquet where the dominant citrus and white-fleshed fruits are threadedwith appealing hints of Mediterranean herbs. On the palate it unfolds over an intriguingly agile structure nicely paced by a well-sustained savouriness.

name: Chianti Classico
description: On the nose you sense the stony minerality along with rose petals, strawberries on the vine and subtle orange spice. The structure is elegant and refined, with lovely fresh, vibrant flavors of pomegranate and bright cherries. The acidity is lively and carries the finish of nutmeg and fresh orange peel.

name: Chianti Classico Riserva
description: The nose exudes ripe plums with spices of nutmeg and cinnamon. There is also an herbal tone of bay leaf and cypress. The mouthfeel has soft and supple tannins with very approachable acids. Flavors explode with lavender, tart raspberries and hints of white pepper. The acids carry the finish of licorice and lingering ripe tangerine.

name: Chianti Classico Strada Al Sasso Riserva
description: This is the most intense, brooding, concentrated, complex wine we produce at Tenuta di Arceno. The aromatics are saturated with dark fruit, dark-roasted coffee beans and violets. The palate is dense and commanding with dried plums, nutmeg, earth, wet slate, firm acids and fine tannins.

name: Silver Tequila 100% de Agave

name: Añejo Tequila 100% De Agave

name: Blanco Tequila 100% de Agave

name: Reposado Tequila 100% de Agave

name: Single Barrel Reposado Tequila
description: One-of-a-kind tequila that goes against the grain in essence and in taste. Aged exclusively in barrels from Sazerac’s award-winning whiskey brands, Corazón Single Barrel is tequila with an inherently provocative twist.

description:

TASTE: The palate has an iodine mineral tone and a creamy texture that fills the mouth and leads into an invigorating, spicy finish.

It is the only natural orange liqueur that is distilled in Mexico and exported to the United States. No artificial flavors or chemical enhancers are ever added. Citronge is excellent straight or in a premium cocktail.

name: Small Batch Blanco Tequila
description: This ultra-premium, small batch tequila was founded by Dwayne “The Rock” Johnson. Crafted in a small Mexican town, amdist the highest peaks of the Jalisco Highlands. Every step of our tequila-making process is meticulously done the right way, by hand, at our distillery. We harvest only fully matured sweet agave, slow roast in traditional brick ovens and distill in handmade custom copper pot stills to produce a bright, flavorful tequila with notes of citrus and a smooth fresh finish.

name: Small Batch Reposado Tequila
description: This ultra-premium, small batch tequila was founded by Dwayne “The Rock” Johnson. Crafted in a small Mexican town, amidst the highest peaks of the Jalisco Highlands. Every step of our tequila-making process is meticulously done the right way by hand at our distillery. We harvest only fully matured sweet agave, slow roast in traditional brick ovens and distill in handmade custom copper pot stills to produce a bright, flavorful tequila with notes of baked pineapple, vanilla and a smooth fresh finish.

name: Small Batch Reposado Tequila
description: This ultra-premium, small batch tequila was founded by Dwayne “The Rock” Johnson. Crafted in a small Mexican town, amidst the highest peaks of the Jalisco Highlands. name: 125 Year Old Vine Zinfandel Deaver Vineyard Amador County
description: The Terra d’Oro Deaver Zinfandel has a deep garnet color with lifted aromas of dark fruit, clove and spicy oak. The palate is focused with crisp and juicy layers of ripe blackberry, spicy plum and soft chewy tannins. The baked spice components add complexity to this bold wine and support a great balance of power and restraint.

name: Barbera Amador County
description: Terra d’Oro Barbera showcases the refreshing acidity of the grape with inviting aromas of sweet red fruit and fresh toasted bread. Enticing flavors of cherry cola and blueberries coat the palate, and polished tannins boast an elegant, round finish. A perfect complement to savory dishes, Terra d’Oro Barbera pairs particularly well with pork roast or orecchiette bolognese.

name: Chenin Blanc Viognier Clarksburg
description: The Terra d’Oro Chenin Blanc & Viognier displays luring aromas of juicy tropical fruits, fresh lemon and hints of spice. The palate boasts flavors of pink grapefruit, papaya, and subtle sweet mango. This wine is lively, refreshing and well balanced with crisp acidity – perfect for a warm afternoon or during sunset hour.

name: Moscato Amador County
description: Terra d'Oro from United States, provided by Sutter Home/Trinchero Family Est. Enjoy the unique taste and quality.

name: Pinot Grigio Santa Barbara County
description: Terra d’Oro Pinot Grigio entices with a nose of ripe, bright pear and clover blossom. Rich and dense, the mouth oozes with juicy pear and stone fruit flavors, finishing with an elegant touch of toasted French oak.

name: Zinfandel Amador County
description: This savory Zinfandel displays vibrant aromas of rich, spicy clove and big, generous fruit with hints of vanilla that entice the nose. An abundance of plums and flavors of dense, juicy blackberries excites the senses with a round mouthfeel of well-integrated tannins on the finish. This wine is rich and powerful, and incredibly well-balanced.

name: Zinfandel Port Amador County
description: While some people say, "any port in a storm", we strongly suggest ours. Terra d'Oro Zinfandel Port displays aromas of raisined berry fruit, sugared dates, chocolate, caramel and orange peel. The wine's rich, lush, grapy flavors also evoke raisin, cocoa, coffee and toffee.

name: Rías Baixas Albariño Abadía de San Campio
description: 100% Albariño from the Appellation D.O. Rías Baixas, Abadía de San Campio contains a higher concentration of flavors and lower acidity, representing a more supple and voluminous style of Albariño. This wine is fruit-forward and lively on the palate, containing aromas of citrus, tropical fruit and freshly-cut green apple. Well-balanced acidity and soft creamy notes make it the perfect accompaniment to sushi, seafood and any kind of spicy food.

name: Rías Baixas O Rosal
description: Flagship wine of Terras Gauda, O Rosal pays homage to the native varieties of Galicia. A unique blend of estate-grown Albariño, Caíño Blanco and Loureiro, each variety plays an important part in this being one of the most sought-after wines from Rias Baixas year-after-year. A wonderfully complex wine with notes of tropical & orchard fruit, intertwined with hints of star anise and crème fraiche.

name: Irpinia Falanghina
description: Offers a rich and intense aroma of fruit with hints of apple, pineapple, quince and pear. It is fresh and clean in the mouth with excellent acidity.

name: Irpinia Rosaenovae Rosé
description:

Bouquet: Elegant with aromatic notes of cherry, red fruits and apricot.
Flavor: Well-balanced, dry and persistent with undertones of peach and an after taste of strawberry.

name: Margarita Mixers
description:
Features the one-of-a-kind flavor profile only available at Texas Roadhouse.
Made with 19% Persian lime juice and blue agave from the Jalisco region of Mexico, blended with orange oils that define this Legendary Margarita in the minds of millions across the globe.

name: 12 Years Old DoubleWood Single Malt Scotch Whisky
description: The Balvenie DoubleWood is a 12 year old single malt which gains its distinctive character from being matured in two wood types. Over the period of maturation it is transferred from a traditional oak whisky cask to a first fill European oak sherry cask. Each stage lends different qualities to the resulting single malt ~ the traditional casks soften and add character, whilst the sherry wood brings depth and fullness of flavour.

name: 14 Years Old Caribbean Cask Single Malt Scotch Whisky
description: The Balvenie Caribbean Cask 14 year old single malt whisky has been matured in traditional oak whisky casks for 14 years, and then ‘finished’ in casks that previously held Caribbean rum.

name: 15 Year Old Single Barrel Sherry Cask Single Malt Scotch Whisky
description:
Nose : Dried fruits overlaid with a gentle nuttiness.
Taste : Rich with elegant oak and subtle spice.
Finish : Long, sherried finish.

name: Brut Blanc de Blancs
description: Generous yet elegant aromas of ripe apple, stone fruit, shortbread and lemon blossom evolve into a rounded and soft palate. A lovely balance between floral and fruit elements underscored by a buttery brioche base note.

name: Brut Cuvée Rosé
description: A whiff of blossom clings to the appetizing hint of freshly cut red-apple peel on the nose of this very pale rosé. The palate adds richness and a touch of honey and chalk that provides a sonorous dimension, filling the mouth with the bounty of ripe, red apples. The mousse is creamy, underlining the ample structure that allows the ripe acidity to swirl alluringly across the palate.

name: 22 Islay Dry Gin
description:
The Botanist is a gin of layered complexity.
A progressive exploration of the botanical heritage of our isle of islay. 22 hand-foraged local botanicals delicately augment nine berries, barks, seeds and peels during an achingly slow distillation. This first and only Islay dry gin is a rare expression of the heart and soul of our remote Scottish island.

name: Cabernet Sauvignon Mt. Veeder
description: The traditional red fruit aromas and flavors of the dominant Cabernet Sauvignon are led by bright cherry and wild mountain raspberry. The addition of our Malbec offers blueberry joined by notes of vanilla, cassis, creamy chocolate caramel and oak spice.

name: Chardonnay Estate Grown Napa Valley
description: The Su’skol Vineyard Chardonnay is carefully farmed with multiple clones to emphasize fruit with wonderful acidity and balance. Crisp and clean, our low oak Chardonnay showcases an aromatic musqué, resulting in aromas and flavors of apple, white pear and a slight touch of tropical fruits, accented by aromas of honeysuckle.

name: Chardonnay Panthera Russian River Valley
description: The word Panthera is believed to be of East Asian origin, meaning ‘the yellowish animal’ or golden-yellow. As a reflection of this moniker, we have crafted a striking golden-yellow Chardonnay that is opulent in style and beautifully textured. Rich and creamy upon entry with notes of lemon curd, crème brulee and candied lemon peel, this wine presents beautiful layers of stone fruit. Unctuous but focused, Panthera Chardonnay offers notes of buttered French toast and hints of well-integrated smoky oak that persist through a satisfying, long finish.

name: Lion Tamer Cabernet Sauvignon Napa Valley
description: Lion Tamer Cabernet Sauvignon is plush in texture with heady aromas of blackberries, black cherries and notes of freshly ground coffee. We add a touch of Malbec to the blend to develop a softness in the tannins, making this a wonderfully smooth and seamless wine. These mouthwatering tannins surround the palate, framing layered elements of bright blueberry, toasty oak and deliciously rich mocha. I find this vintage of Lion Tamer Cabernet is perfectly balanced, with well-integrated vanilla oak notes presenting on the lengthy, elegant finish.

name: Lion Tamer Red Napa Valley
description: The signature of Lion Tamer is a generous palate of black raspberry and surprisingly lush tannins. Malbec serves as our “tannin tamer” in this wine, but on its own brings heady floral aromas of violets and bold, juicy flavors upon entry. Layering in Zinfandel, Petite Sirah and Cabernet Sauvignon create complex notes of black plum and blackcurrant with subtle elements of cocoa. The wine’s plush texture and ripe, juicy core of black fruit are brightened by of Mourvèdre that delivers the perfect amount of cheerful red fruit. The blend together creates a wine with delicious notes of black plum, cassis and boysenberry that are concentrated in the mid-palate and enveloped in bright cherry notes that deliver a graceful elegance and balanced finish.

name: Pinot Noir Shirtail Ranches Central Coast
description: Pinot Noir is always a go-to for me – whether as a wine by the glass or with dinner and friends. This wine has volume, a big luscious mouthfeel, followed by layers of cinnamon, cherry and raspberry fruits. Hints of vanilla and beautifully soft tannins highlight the deep cherry jam and vanilla evident in this intense, darkly colored Pinot. The mouth-filling taste is like velvet, demonstrating what gentle handling can do for this variety.

name: Sauvignon Blanc Shirtail Ranches North Coast
description: This wine is loaded with aromatics of grapefruit and lemon grass with a hint of lime zest in the background. Refreshing acidity and citrus notes lead into a racy mouth that boasts notes of fresh fig and jasmine. This is a great warm weather wine with ample acidity and will pair nicely with a wide variety of cuisines; my favorite pairing is with oysters on the half shell.

name: The Lioness Chardonnay Estate Grown Napa Valley
description: The Lioness is dynamic and beautifully balanced with a lush texture that is complemented by a core of acidity running throughout. Layered flavors of tropical fruit and a hint of smoke integrate with notes of nutmeg and almond. These delicious elements of toasty oak persist throughout a long satisfying finish.

name: Cuvéee Sinso Central Coast
description: The Language of Yes from United States, provided by E & J Gallo Winery. Enjoy the unique taste and quality.

name: Les Fruits Rouges A Pink Wine Central Coast
description: The Language of Yes from United States, provided by E & J Gallo Winery. Enjoy the unique taste and quality.

name: Syrah En Passerillage Rancho Réal Vineyard Santa Maria Valley
description: This latest project by Randall Grahm involves picking grapes a bit early and then drying them a tad before fermentation. In this wine, that leads to aromas of charred meat, tar, violet and purple fruits on the nose. Similar elements emerge on the sip, with açai and black pepper proving most prominent as the wine spreads its wings.

name: 12 Years Old Double Cask Highland Single Malt Scotch Whisky
description:
Nose : Creamy butterscotch, candied orange and vanilla custard.

Taste : Honey, spices and citrus, balanced with raisins and caramel.

name: 12 Years Old Highland Single Malt Scotch Whisky
description: Exclusively matured in selected sherry oakcasks from jerez.

name: 18 Years Old Sherry Oak Highland Single Malt Scotch Whisky
description:
Speyside, Scotland - Outstanding, complex single malt, matured at The Macallan distillery for a minimum of 18 years in selected sherry oak casks from Spain. Rich palate of dried fruits, spice, orange and toasted oak.

Soft and rich, with hints of spice, clove, orange & toasted mature oak

name: Rare Cask Highland Single Malt Scotch Whisky 86 Proof
description:
Color : Ruby Red.
Nose : Soft notes of opulent vanilla and raisin give way to a sweet ensemble of apple, lemon, and orange. All balanced by a spicy quartet of root ginger, cinnamon, nutmeg and clove.
Palate : This spicy quartet are unwavering. Oak resonates, timeless, polished and rich. Vanilla and chocolate lead the finale along with a light citrus zest.
Finish : Warming and woody.

name: Single Malt Irish Whiskey
description: Made from 100% irish malted barley, the sexton is triple distilled in copper pot stills and aged in former oloroso sherry casks. The result is a perfect balance of rich, dried fruits and subtle oak notes with a smooth finish.

name: Cabernet Sauvignon California
description:
A deep red, nearly purple color, with aromatics of concentrated black fruits, cigar
box and notes of barrel toast. Dark fruit, spice and rich flavors continue on the palate.
Quite brooding, but pure and focused. The tannins are super integrated and soft, but
with terrific balance and finish that gives it unusual length in the palate.

name: Malbec Mendoza
description: A deep red, nearly purple color, with aromatics of concentrated black fruits, cigar box and notes of barrel toast. Dark fruit, spice and rich flavors continue on the  palate. Quite brooding, but pure and focused. The tannins are super integrated and  soft, but with terrific balance and finish that gives it unusual length in the palate.

name: Glendullan 12 Years Old Single Malt Scotch Whiskey 80 Proof
description: This 12 Years Old Single Malt aged in predominately American oak casks, with a touch of European oak, this 12 years old has fresh fruit aromas, a sweet honeyed palate & Creamy lingering finish.

name: Glendullan 15 Years Old Single Malt Scotch Whiskey 80 Proof
description:
Nose : Sweet, soft and inviting. Mild at first with traces of spice and sweet wood followed by richer mature notes.

Finish : Smooth, with light toasty oak, well balanced, with a creamy violet scented notes.

Body : Medium to full.

Palate : Soft and lightly sweet with buttery fruit cake mix followed by hints of citrus soft fruit and vanilla with a dry finish.

name: Glendullan 18 Years Old Sublimely Smooth Single Malt Scotch Whiskey 80 Proof
description:
Nose : Dry, rich and complex with a mild nose-feel, backed by black pepper and mature notes of cigar box.

Finish : Soft, dry and rounded. Adding water allows a pleasant, nutty spiciness to come through, recalling the cigar-box found on the nose, while there’s a cooling aftertaste.

Body : Medium to full.

Palate : Smooth rich texture with sweet citrus notes balanced by chocolate, cherry and chili notes.

name: Zinfandel Lodi
description: A truly otherworldly Zinfandel, this wine transcends the ordinary. Heady aromas of ripe black cherries and warm cinnamon reveal bold blackberry and spiced plum flavors cloaked in toasted vanilla. Smooth and full-bodied with a lingering finish, this distinctive Zinfandel is a versatile, expressive wine. Whether you enjoy it on its own or with food, The Specialyst is an out-of-this world experience.

name: Small Batch Irish Whiskey
description: Teeling's Flagship Irish whiskey and attempt to create the most interesting Blended Irish whiskey. This small batch bottling consists of hand selected casks which are given further maturation in ex-rum barrels imparting extra character and smooth flavor unique to Irish whiskey. Bottling at 46% with no chill filtration completes an Irish whiskey of true character.

name: Single Malt Irish Whisky 80 Proof

description: The 2014 Cab Franc is rich, yet bright with red and blackberry style fruit, plush textured tannins, and well integrated French oak. With a 10% splash of Cabernet Sauvignon, this wine is showing well now but can hold on for years.

Triple distilled for extra smoothness, our blend is a choice of the finest Irish Malt and Grain whiskeys.

description:

Body : Round with creamy tones.
Finish : Dry with hints of sherry and spices from the Oloroso barrel cask.

Palate : The creaminess from the cocoa follows through, pairing beautifully with the subtle coffee tones. This is rounded out by hints of caramel.
Finish : Long, lingering with a creamy mouthfeel.

name: Oloroso Irish Whisky Sherry Cask Finish
description:
Aroma : Dry sherbet lemon, white grape, walnut nougat with creamy raspberry and a hint of tropical fruits.
Body : Bergamot orange, mouth-coating nougat, a slight minerality, tied together with a hint of coconut, banana and a brief pear note.
Finish : Sweet, lingering finish with a dry wood prickle flavors from the Oloroso Sherry cask.
